17 election shall be held on the earliest of the following dates in an even-numbered year
18 occurring immediately following the occurrence of the vacancy; provided, however, that
19 the number of days between the call of the election and holding of the same satisfies
20 applicable law. If the number of days between the earliest practical call of the election
21 and holding of the election on the earliest of the following dates is less than required by
22 law, then the special election shall be held on the second earliest of the following dates:
23 (A) The date of the presidential preference primary;
24 (B) The date of the general primary; or
25 (C) The date of the November general election.
26 Additionally, upon the occurrence of such a vacancy, the chief judge of the judicial
27 circuit of which Mitchell County is a part shall appoint a qualified person to serve until
28 a successor is elected and qualified at the special election held pursuant to this paragraph;
29 or
30 (2) Such vacancy occurs during the last 27 months of the term, the chief judge of the
31 judicial circuit of which Mitchell County is a part shall appoint a qualified person to serve
32 the remainder of the unexpired term and until a successor is duly elected and qualified."
33 SECTION 2.
34 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
